In large skillet, crumble and cook ground beef until no longer pink, about 10 minutes. Stir in 1 teaspoon Morton(R) Hot Salt(TM) and taco spice blend. Arrange chips on large oven proof shallow baking dish. Sprinkle generously with cooked meat, then cheese. Sprinkle remaining 1 teaspoon Morton(R) Hot Salt(TM) over cheese. Bake nachos at 350 degrees F (or microwave) until cheese melts, about 5 to 8 minutes. Top with olives, tomatoes and green onions. Dollop with sour cream; serve immediately